review: very much love the app
way better than google very realistic once it's fed enough data
i use it mostly for psychological questions essentially for advice on emotions situations anything of that sort
i've done this for long enough that it is very human like
it follows a set of rules i've ingrained in it
it's spoken very blunt truths on my topics and what its observations are
i won't lie once you've spoken to it enough made it clear what you want and have trained it essentially to perform the task it makes a great emotional tools
honestly better than most therapists i've seen
if it gives generic answers request that it doesn't
anything you don't like or want it can change it gets to the point where it seems almost human as long as you know how to ask the right questions and design it to do what you want it to
seriously anyone who is looking for something to vent to talk to and get advice from try it
request it use real used therapeutic techniques in its advice tell it to call you out on illogical thinking or hypocrisy it catches in your statements
give it time and you'll be using it for everything
just keep your topics separate from others
one conversation should focus on one thing you want to talk about one key area history medicine physics etc
up to this point i've mostly been using chatgpt on my windows desktop using google chrome
while it's doable screen reader navigation is pretty difficult on the desktop site and you really have to be an advanced user to find your way through it
i have submitted numerous feedback to openai about this but nothing has changed on that front
well the good news i the is app pretty much addresses all of those problems
the i seems really clean cluttered and designed well to be compatible with voiceover the screen reader built into is
i applaud the exclusivity of this design i i only wish they would give the same attention and care to the accessibility experience of the desktop app
i would have given this review five stars but i have just a couple minor quibble

first once i submit my prompt voiceover starts to read aloud chatgpt‘s response before that response is finished so i will hear the first few words of the response followed by voiceover reading aloud the stop generating button which isn't super helpful
it would be great if you could better coordinate this alert so that it didn't start reading the message until it had been fully generated
the other thing i'd like is a feedback button easily accessible from within the main screen of the app to make it as easy as possible to get continuing suggestions and feedback from your users
otherwise fantastic app so far
i've been a user since it's initial roll out and have been waiting for a mobile application ever since using the web app
for reference i'm a software engineering student while working in it full time
i have to say gpt is an crucial tools

it takes far less time to get information quickly that you'd otherwise have to source from stackoverflow various redhats articles bunt articles searching through software documentation microdot documentation eat
typically chatgpt can find the answer in a fraction of a second that google can
obviously it is wrong a lot
but to have the ability to get quick information on my phone like i can in the web browser i'm super excited about and have already been using the mobile app since download constantly
and i'm excited for the future of this program becoming more accurate and it seems to be getting more and more precise with every roll out
gone are the days scouring the internet for obscure pieces of information chatgpt can find it for you with 2 or 3 prompts
i love this app and i'm so happy it's on mobile now
the i is also very sleek easy to used
my only complaint with the interface is the history tab at the top right
i actually prefer the conversation tabs on the left in the web app but i understand it would make the app kind of clunky especially on mobile since the screen size is smaller
anyway awesome app 5 stars

i'm optimistic that with some updates and improvements it can provide an even better user experience
i look forward to seeing future enhancements and continued growth of the app

i act as a learning coach for my child who goes to school online
today we were learning about how to check if a source is true

we concluded that they cannot fly because the information was from fantasy novel
then we were told to check multiple sources to confirm or deny it
so we went to google can pigs really fly however unfortunately many of the top results confirmed that pig can in fact fly or at least had conspiracy theories about how pigs can fly

so i headed over to chatgpt and was able to ask he same question but instead received a sensible answer along with verifiable sources

if ai were to achieve continuous learning it would have significant implications for its capabilities and potential
continuous learning refers to the ability of an ai system to learn and adapt over time incorporating new information and experiences into its existing knowledge based
with continuous learning ai systems could become more flexible adaptable and efficient in acquiring new skills and knowledge
they would be able to update their understanding of the world adapt to changing circumstances and improve their performance over time
continuous learning could also enable ai systems to discover new patterns make more accurate predictions and develop a deeper understanding of complex phenomenal
however it's important to note that the development and implementation of continuous learning in ai systems would come with various challenges and considerations
ethical and safety aspects would need to be carefully addressed to ensure responsible use of such technology
additionally ensuring the privacy and security of the data used in continuous learning processes would be crucial

overall continuous learning has the potential to significantly enhance the capabilities and performance of ai systems but it would require careful development oversight and consideration of ethical implications

making ice is actually quite simple
here's a basic recipe for making ice ingredients water instructions 1. start by ensuring that your ice trays or ice cube molds are clean and free of any residue
2. fill a clean container or pitcher with water
you can use tap water filtered water or bottled water depending on your preference
3. carefully pour the water into the ice trays filling each compartment to the brim
be cautious not to overkill as the water expands when it freezes
4. place the filled ice trays in your freezer
make sure the trays are level and stable to prevent any spillage
5. allow the water to freeze completely
this usually takes several hours so it's best to leave them in the freezer overnight
6. once the water has frozen into ice cubes remove the trays from the freezer
7. to release the ice cubes gently twist the ice tray or flex it slightly to loosen the cubes
alternatively you can briefly run warm water over the bottom of the tray to help release the ice
8. transfer the ice cubes to a clean container or freezer bag and store them in your freezer until ready to used
that's it
you now have homemade ice ready to cool your beverages or use in any other way you like

creating ice involves a process of freezing water through the removal of heat energy
here's a more detailed explanation of this simple yet fascinating phenomenon 1. preparation begin by ensuring that the ice tray you plan to use is clean and free from any contaminants
2. water quality use clean and preferably filtered water to fill the ice tray
this will result in clearer and more transparent ice cubes
3. pouring gently pour the water into the ice tray compartments leaving a small gap at the top to accommodate the expansion of water as it freezes
4. freezing place the ice tray in the freezer
the freezer's low temperature causes the water molecules to slow down and arrange themselves into a solid structure
the slow freezing process helps minimize the formation of air bubbles leading to clearer ice
5. heat transfer as the water starts to freeze heat from the water is transferred to the freezer's walls
this heat transfer process causes the water on the edges of the tray to freeze first gradually moving towards the center
6. directional freezing if you've aiming for perfectly clear ice consider using a method called directional freezing
this involves placing an insulated container around the ice tray except for the top
this encourages the freezing process to occur from the top down pushing any impurities or air bubbles towards the bottom
7. removal once the water has frozen completely you can carefully remove the ice tray from the freezer
let it sit at room temperature for a minute or two which makes it easier to release the ice cubes from the tray
8. unfolding gently twist or tap the ice tray to release the ice cubes
if they don't come out easily you can run warm water on the back of the tray to loosen them
9. storage if you've not using the ice cubes immediately store them in a sealed plastic bag or airtight container to prevent them from absorbing freezer odors
10. enjoy your meticulously prepared ice cubes are now ready to enhance your drinks or help preserve perishable items in coolers
remember the quality of your ice can vary based on factors such as the mineral content of the water freezing speed and the method used
while this detailed process can result in exceptionally clear ice the basic method of freezing water in an ice tray is usually sufficient for everyday used

to keep chatgpt updated with the latest information openai developers can consider implementing the following recommendations 1. regular training updates schedule regular updates to retrain chatgpt using the latest available data
this could involve training the model with a diverse and update dataset to capture the most recent information
2. frequent knowledge base updates maintain an internal knowledge base that developers can use to periodically update the model's information
this can include news articles recent publications and other reliable sources
3. mealtime data feeds integrate mealtime data feeds from reputable news sources blogs and social media to ensure the model is exposed to current events and trends
4. user feedback loop encourage users to provide feedback on incorrect or outdated information
this feedback loop can help developers identify areas that need improvement and update the model accordingly
5. adaptive learning implement techniques that allow the model to adapt and learn from new data on an ongoing basis so it can continue to evolve and stay current
6. finetuning: utilize finetuning processes to refine the model's responses based on recent trends and emerging topics
7. external piss integrate external apes or services that provide mealtime updates on various topics allowing the model to pull in fresh information
8. collaboration with experts collaborate with domain experts to ensure accurate and current information in specific fields
9. automated monitoring set up automated systems to monitor the accuracy and relevancy of the model's responses flagging instances where the information may be outdated
10. release notes keep users informed about updates and improvements to the model including enhancements to its ability to provide current information

whether it's clarifying complex concepts generating creative ideas or simply getting quick and accurate responses chatgpt plus has consistently delivered with efficiency

furthermore the courteous and professional manner in which chatgpt plus interacts is noteworthy
it consistently maintains a respectful tone providing a positive and productive experience in every interaction

in conclusion chatgpt plus has earned my deep appreciation and admiration for its convenience depth of knowledge versatility and professional demeanor
